title: Intermediate structure in the neutron scattering cross sections of iron

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.210, p.51 (1973)
Conf: Nuclear Data for Reactors Conf., Helsinki 1970, Vol.2, p.301 (1970)

x4freetext: Intermediate structure in the neutron scattering
JAERI 5.5 MeV Van De Graaff and Mobley
Tritium target was a gas cell about 3 cm
long and was filled with tritium gas at 42 cm Hg.
hollow cylinder, long 4 cm, inner diameter
1.5 cm, outer diameter 2.5 cm, weight 98.6 gr.
2 inch high, viewed by a XP-1040 photomultiplier,
.Neutrons and the 0.845 MeV gamma ray from 26-Fe-56
detected by the same detector, no discrimination
.for the elastic and inelastic scattering a Monte Carlo
.The effect of the multiple scattering on the gamma
angular distribution was corrected by an analytical
method similar to the one used by S.A.Cox,
